<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=24822#M24822">177</a> of 209
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 411 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P></P>
<HR>
Grizzlesnozz wrote:
<P><FONT color=#ccff00>I agreed that Knights should be able to tank their regular progression content reliably. However, what content are you talking about? it sounds like you're saying that no content should exist that challenges dps beyond your level of knight progression? No, I said knights should not be able to reliably tank ALL of the content at a given level of progression. </FONT></P>
<P>Hrmm.... How can I make this any more clear to you? What content am I talking about? A time level knight should be able to tank all content geared towards time level groups... reliably. A Qvic level knight should be able to tank all content geared towards Qvic level groups.... reliably. A CoA level knight should be able to tank all content geared toward CoA level groups.... reliably. See where I'm heading with this? I'm saying that group content should NOT be balanced based on what warriors are capable of because then the only viable tank (atleast to begin with) is a Warrior. You think that knights should not be able to tank all content at a given progression level even with appropriate gear apparently so we'll just have to disagree here. It's not suprising you want knights to have to over gear to manage things but that's not how it should work.</P>
<P><FONT color=#ccff00>I think defensive should be replaced by a larger innate difference between warrior and knight classes. it makes it difficult to balance content for both. However, if defensive is our primary tool that shows significant difference in mitigation than it should be needed in group content. The problem is how to make it needed without making knights less desirable. The way to do it imo is much like they have often done in the past... All mobs in an area hitting for the same amount is boring anyways. Add some mean bruisers who like to hit hard. Add an occasional mobs that takes knightly devotion to withstand spiritual attack other than dps. Not every group needs to be able to kill every mob in their local progression area. Some they should come back later for. Some they should seek out extra healing, or, extra tanking for. Having some interesting mobs who's threat level is signifcantly higher than average adds to the game, is fun and much the reason I ever enjoyed playing a warrior. </FONT><BR></P>
<P>Should every group be able to kill everything within a certain level of progression? Certainly not. Should a well balanced appropriately geared group with a Knight tank have the opportunity if well played to kill whatever they want at their level of progression and not have an excessive chance of failure for no other reason then the tank is a Knight? Absolutely. Sure there should be some hard hitters here and there but that should be the exception not the rule. The vast majority of content should be fairly uniformly challenging and event based content. Hard hitting should also not be defined based on a defensive warrior being pushed to his limits and everyone else dying, and no defensive shouldn't be replaced by a massive all the time gap because that doesn't have the limits and/or penalties defensive has.</P>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
