		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<i><b>Should a well balanced appropriately geared group with a Knight tank
have the opportunity if well played to kill whatever they want at their
level of progression and not have an excessive chance of failure for no
other reason then the tank is a Knight?<br></b></i>Knights have always been able to tank appropriate content. It just doesn't happen to be the same appropriate content a Warrior might tank.<br><br>Ya see you start out with a misrepresentation - that Knight tanking is intended to be the same as Warrior tanking. It isn't.<br><br><i><b></b><b>Sure there should be some hard hitters here and there but that should
be the exception not the rule. The vast majority of content should be
fairly uniformly challenging and event based content.</b></i><br><br>Sure, there should be a couple of mobs needing to be pulled in every expansion, but that should be the exception not the rule. Players should rarely die and need a res, want clerical buffs when a Druid or Shaman is the group's mainhealer - mobs shouldn't debuff you and buffs should never wear off, or need a heal.<br><br>Don't you mean to say, the vast majority of content should give Knights Tank Parity (and Spellbook Superiority).<br><br><i><b>Hard hitting should also not be defined based on a defensive warrior being pushed to his limits and everyone else dying<br></b></i>That's what hard hitting <u>is</u> sir. Unmatched survivability means doing a bodycount. It's never meant <u>everyone</u> else dying. Even with GoD trials adjusted 5 levels too hard some Knights - wearing the previous expansion's gear TANKED (not stood there and watched a Ranger WS, but actually tanked) and won.<br><br>Should any group content be designed so only a small handful of Knights can manage it when it's first encountered? IMO 6 is too small a number, but 100 <u>might</u> be reasonable. Afterall, endgame raid content isn't exactly beaten by every Tom, **SMURF**, and Harry. Why should endgame group content be any different. The late bloomers will beat it sometime down the road if they persist. Heck, right now some guilds are just breaking into PoTime sir (I'm not belittling breaking into PoTime - those that do so have accomplished a major in-game milestone and we ALL salute you).<br><div></div>	
