Grizzlesnozz wrote:
<p><font color="#ccff00">I agreed that Knights should be able to tank their regular progression content reliably. However, what content are you talking about? it sounds like you're saying that no content should exist that challenges dps beyond your level of knight progression? No, I said knights should not be able to reliably tank ALL of the content at a given level of progression. </font></p>

<p>Hrmm.... How can I make this any more clear to you? What content am I talking about? A time level knight should be able to tank all content geared towards time level groups... reliably. A Qvic level knight should be able to tank all content geared towards Qvic level groups.... reliably. A CoA level knight should be able to tank all content geared toward CoA level groups.... reliably. See where I'm heading with this? I'm saying that group content should NOT be balanced based on what warriors are capable of because then the only viable tank (atleast to begin with) is a Warrior. You think that knights should not be able to tank all content at a given progression level even with appropriate gear apparently so we'll just have to disagree here. It's not suprising you want knights to have to over gear to manage things but that's not how it should work.<br></p><p><font color="#ccff00">No, I merely think group content should be challenging for aplayers of all progression levels. If warriors have an advantage in mitigation that helps them survive better than knights then when the content is challenging enough it will come into play. If you feel that a Qvic level tank should never be challenged until he magically gears up to the next level, i don't know what to tell you. progression isn't broken into cleanly defined boundaries for individual players. Start with nothing collect gear from various levels of play and progress. As they progress they should be challenged. At any given point during progression something should be too hard to tank. Everyone should need to progress to tank it. Warriors of equal progression will be able to tank chellenging mobs whose main threat is dps before knights given equal healing resource. That's nothing new and it is intended in EQ. If you want to argue exact balance difference that's something else. <br></font></p><font color="#ccff00">Yes, I do think there should be some mobs in group content with unusually high dps threat. No, I do not think they should be placed as blocks in places like group flag progression and spell missions that knights need to tank for progression.</font><br><p></p>Should every group be able to kill everything within a certain level of progression? Certainly not. Should a well balanced appropriately geared group with a Knight tank have the opportunity if well played to kill whatever they want at their level of progression and not have an excessive chance of failure for no other reason then the tank is a Knight? Absolutely. Sure there should be some hard hitters here and there but that should be the exception not the rule. The vast majority of content should be fairly uniformly challenging and event based content. Hard hitting should also not be defined based on a defensive warrior being pushed to his limits and everyone else dying, and no defensive shouldn't be replaced by a massive all the time gap because that doesn't have the limits and/or penalties defensive has.
<hr>
</blockquote><font color="#ccff00">I never said massive, those are your words. <br><br><font color="#ccff00">I'm not sure whether you are agreeing with me, or, not here. That's basically what I said, exceptionally high dps mobs as exceptions, not the rule, with knights being able to tank through progression for their groups. That doesn't mean that those regular group mobs shouldn't offer reasonable dps challenge. I mean going to a new zone and multipulling the tougest xp mobs we find is kinda gimped. Chanters, puillers, tanks and even heavy healers are all marginalized to a degree.<br><br>I disagree with what kind of challenge hard dps mobs should offer. They should vary like most other content, have personality and distinction. There should almos always be some mobs in my group content&nbsp; that require me to use everything i have in order to survive dps while being supported by a strong group of my level. Challenge shouldn't stop at you, because that's where you feel comfortable with it. Challenge should extend to cover all players and classes doing their utmost.<br></font> </font></blockquote><br></div><p>Message Edited by Grizzlesnozz on <span class=date_text>08-05-2006</span> <span class=time_text>07:01 PM</span>	
