			>
			<div></div><div></div><p>"<i>And the difference is that each of those 2 classes here have
different idea's they gear for in a raid.A SHD wants clean consise
regular damage for as low as possible. Even at max ac a raid named will
still spike, there designed to do so as the spike damage is what
usually kills you. Think we both know in&nbsp;group content a raider, even
using there base ac off there items will still be higher ac than what
the content was designed for generally.But looking at the past
itemization we can also assume that history shows that wars generally
had more AC in those items over other classes. So for them to gear for
HP and make that a focus isnt that insane a premise.</i>"<br>
<br>
I do wonder what you mean by max AC, as Igneous is proof that enough
warrior AC coupled with debuffs means many mobs hit minimum/lower end DI so much,
that they are lucky to get a single max hit, and that the chance for
spike hits of DI's 16-20 are all less than 0.5% (afaik, with max being
in triple decimal figures- that said I would kill to get some of his
logs /tap).<br>
<br>
<i>So this is why I support the OP's idea here, because it does make
sense. He put forth this idea to state that the relative difference's
between the tank classes have caused a blurring, id say thats rather
accurate. Where as I dont feel the DI increases would yield the results
he was looking for, I do belive his assessment in AC is worth a look
and possible itemization as since we are begining to all wear the same
armor it is a way to ensure a slight class advantage which was always
the case except in recent times. Whether you view this as class greed
or not, id say its a rather fair assesment and doubtfull a more consise
look could be done, but we could look at full numbers of the AC sets
and count how many AC augments that would have been relativly naturally
worn by such classes.<br>
</i></p>

<p>An small increase in return would have the same benefit as
increasing the base rAC on warrior specific items, even more so when
factoring in buff ac ofc. Just stating, a small return increase would
be better, if such an increase was needed, because it covers everything.</p>
<p><i>Placing in AC may not do anything great really, but it doesnt
increase the effectivness of Defensive aswell as it doesnt remove a 1
round from a raid named so Id think of the 2 idea's projected 1 would
be favored by knight classes over the other. But to say neither idea
has merit, Isnt exactly a fair assesment its more of just wanting to
retain what you might deem the new Knight advantage. AC<br>
</i></p>
<p>Whilst it doesn't increase the effectiveness of Def, high AC and
Evasive are a sick combination and they really do compliment each
other, even if both are putting you subject to RNG. AC is a warrior
advantage too... as I've always said, Igneous is proof.<br>
</p>
