		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Lluianae wrote:
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<P><FONT color=#ccffff>I do wonder what you mean by max AC, as Igneous is proof that enough warrior AC coupled with debuffs means many mobs hit minimum/lower end DI so much, that they are lucky to get a single max hit, and that the chance for spike hits of DI's 16-20 are all less than 0.5% (afaik, with max being in triple decimal figures- that said I would kill to get some of his logs /tap).<BR></FONT>I Was referring to MAX AC as placing an AC augment in every available slot, as many Knights do this. Basically stateing doing so will lower&nbsp;a warriors max health more than the HP would assist with spike damage. Where as having every available AC augment may reduce average damage from 500-650 range to a consistant 550 as example you will still recieve the high end spikes that are designed into many raid encounters. Placing higher hp is a design to be able to survive these spikes as in some encounters spike damage isnt just a possiblity, its assured. And although i dont belive everything in the War class description building hp to unheard of levels is pretty accurate of the classes power.<BR><I>.</I><FONT color=#ccffff>An small increase in return would have the same benefit as increasing the base rAC on warrior specific items, even more so when factoring in buff ac ofc. Just stating, a small return increase would be better, if such an increase was needed, because it covers everything.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#cccccc>As the OP stated of wishing to raise the AC return slightly, I would agree it would help in many situation group content mostly. But raiding warriors generally equip for the raid scenerio's more than the group ones.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ccffff>Whilst it doesn't increase the effectiveness of Def, high AC and Evasive are a sick combination and they really do compliment each other, even if both are putting you subject to RNG. AC is a warrior advantage too... as I've always said, Igneous is proof.<BR></FONT><FONT color=#ccffff></FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ccffff><FONT color=#cccccc>Where having more ac does make the hits more regular the differences in defensive are not staggering. if we use an example just for easily explained purposes of def cutting damage by 50% for example only. A 5k hit halfed to 2.5k is very good. A average 1k hit halfed to 500 is also effective, but you must have high enough hp to withstand the spike damage in either scenerio which happens quite abit in named raid content.</FONT></FONT></P>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>Message Edited by Lluianae on <SPAN class=date_text>08-06-2006</SPAN><SPAN class=time_text>08:32 AM</SPAN><BR></P>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>Chriten	
