			I'd want to see a long term quality case study on that Lu. Generally, warrior gear is itemized to give good ac returns on high hp stuff and the primary decision comes in augging. The amount of times that warriors get overhealed especially in the days of spam healing is incredible. The more they can gain from that healing the better. the parses I've seen show very little predictable return on high AC past a certain point for a given mob in a particular set of content. Even on someone like Draygun with a couple shadows in him hehe. You do not want to be short on AC for the content in question. Below a certain point it has much stronger relative effect. Above a certain point the gains you make seem small and hard to parse relaibly. I'm all for a balanced approach, although, i've always though AC is more kewl hehe. Imo, too much focus on AC though and you short change your club as a MT. Not that i really care even as a GL, so long as folks are having fun.<br><div></div>	
