			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=98953'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Races/high_elf.jpg" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=24853#M24853">192</a> of 209
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 266 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I just want to highlight one point- "<i>The amount of times that warriors get overhealed especially in the days
of spam healing is incredible. The more they can gain from that healing
the better. the parses I've seen show very little predictable return on
high AC past a certain point for a given mob in a particular set of
content.</i>"<br>
<br>
Firstly, well, opinions may differ about this, but as a heal leader,
when I design healing strats, especially when I am designing a CH chain
(omg we use CH), I make it so that it snugly fits the generic DPS
output of the mob for all the tanks (its silly to make a specific chain
per tank ofc), but in doing so, with the goal of having the AHpM of
each CH, or rather, the average heal of CH to be always over 5-6k (and
minimising Duds), which is very efficient for what youre asking for, in
the realistic world no mob does perfect damage so that CH lands for the
same value each time, if they were that predictable, this would be very
boring <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><br>
<br>
When it comes to spam healing, overhealing is easily minimised by
having healers who pay attention to heal messages in channels / other
places. Whilst it is virtually inevitable, and happens the more healers
you have present, it is still possible to do, such that inefficiency
with heals landing is reduced to near non-existant status, if people
are overhealing then they need to be more reliant on letting others
cast to get efficient heals in also, its not a race, unless the tank is
at dangerously low HP of course. Ditto with DI's, fastest finger helps
there, but if multiple cast then a team can adjust so that whoever is
acknowledged as the first caster remains casting, whilst the others
announce themselves ducking, with the caster saying "held". Thats how
we do it at least. Anyways, heal approaches and mechanics aside <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-tongue.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><br>
<br>
I can see if I can gather more parses with him tanking, and collate
them into statistically viable logs (of over 60 mins per mob, lets say)
just to compare his ac, hes an interesting Case is our troll, because
no one else can see the results personally that he can. I've always
asked if people wanted more info but no one has said anything... until
now <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> as part of the case study what would you like to see shown?<br>
<br>
I'll still say I'm all for an adequate balance, I know which tanks tank what better <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><br>
