<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Lluianae wrote:<BR>In fact one could effectively camp more than 5 25/25s (Stonewarden and shard, I haven't counted the slots they can go in), as well as the 30 aug from Valdoon (which is dead easy to do) things like that on top of whats already mentioned, its true AC is far easier to achieve than getting all the super high hp raid augs, of which are subject to your guilds distribution system and not exp group rules.<BR><BR>There is a point where extra may seem pointless, you've already achieved the basic level of survivability, but I know it can and does help, its just tradition that when this happens you should focus on HP more, and thats where being balanced comes into play. But since this is a thread about mitigation, I thought I'd stick to the AC side /shrug.<BR>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Understandable, but as many knights have said, WAR should focus or have the opurtunity to focus on AC directly. Well as you say its all balance, really once you factor Gear AC you can go well beyond what is really usefull. HP is HP is HP, there are many modifers we have in the War class that greatly increase the return we have off this componet, yet there is also as the op mentioned a reduction in items that were war only that had more AC in fact than the ratio in which they have today in relation to the other tank lines. The proposal he had made was a way to achieve a balance we had as a class previously which has diminished greatly do to poor itemization. Im not saying your wrong lass, im saying the point of this discussion has blurred a great deal back to the original premise for it.<BR></P>
<P>Aswell as the pure pursuit of hp, you lose other valued modifers War use for the basis of control which is our dps, swing rate and hate based off these principles, either way you can imbalance a situation the balance is the thing everyone seeks to perfect and most of it is personal preferance.</P>
