		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div></div>I don't believe Warirors need any special dispensation with something like a Heavy Armor AA ability that grants us 500AC nor "-5 DI".<br><br>Our unmatched ability to <u>survive</u> has always been:<br><br>1. Brief invunerability to melee damage while still being able to tank and hold aggro - something hybrid Knights should <u>never</u> receive.<br><br>2. Dramatic but finite endurance fueled disciplines - something that <u>never</u> should have been shared with hybrid Knights.<br><br>3. A modest (all things concidered) passive tank superiority with little ability to improve it other than by using the disciplines noted above that Knights can equal - by spending mana that they would otherwise be spending on "utility".<br><br>It's intentionally <u>un</u>balanced.<br><br>Yes, as long as there's a range of content "brutality" there will be Warriors that "take the lead" in successfully beating it. We're supposed to.<br><br>Yes, spellbook versatility allows Knights to completely trivialize lesser content that Warriors still find somewhat challanging. It's inevitable. Where Knights are tanking content they can handle they provide utility.<br><br>It's what we chose - bitter and sweet.<br><br>But it the intended gap can never be closed sufficiently that a Knight would dream of aggroing and trying to tank a raid boss mob while a Tank still lives. Warriors don't res, cleric buff, nor heal with a Paladin present. Warriors don't pull where an SK is available.<br><br>Nor can challanging content be so absent from the raid or group environment that the Central Distinguishing Warrior Class Characteristic - unmatched survivability exists no where. Survivability isn't parsing for an hour to see who needed less healing, it's counting bodies.<br><br>Nor can Knight superiority in lesser group content be so great Warriors don't bother logging on except for raids and non-raiding players are stupid to play a Warrior.<br><br>Knight intended tanking inferiority does not equal lack of viability. A host of players don't tank as well a Headboss and the other longtime top tanks - yet they are perfectly viable.<br><div></div><p>Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on <span class=date_text>08-06-2006</span> <span class=time_text>05:16 AM</span>	
		</td></tr>
